article.headline: Miami 76, Norfolk State 58
article.story: CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) -- Robert Hite scored 22 points and Miami beat Norfolk State 76-58 for its eighth consecutive win Sunday. After a sluggish start, Miami broke the game open with a 16-2 run that gave the Hurricanes a 32-14 lead with 6:31 remaining in the first half. Hite and guard Guillermo Diaz combined to score 12 of those 16 points. Diaz finished with 18 points, including 13 in the first half, which saw Miami take a 43-30 lead behind 57.1-percent shooting. Hite scored 13 of his 22 points in the second half, which saw the Hurricanes shoot just 38.5 percent. But Norfolk State shot just 35.6 percent for the game and connected on only 29.4 percent of its field goals in the second half. Karandick Ogunride scored 16 points and Chakowby Hicks added 15 for Norfolk State (3-7). The loss dropped the Spartans' road record to 0-6. The game was the final non-conference contest of the season for Miami. The Hurricanes begin play in the Atlantic Coast Conference for the first time Thursday night at Georgia Tech.
